The paper deals with communication protocols in the presence of an eavesdropper, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of multipath networks suggests a focus on networked systems (cs.NI), and the notion of deniability and hidability may involve concepts from data structures (cs.DS) and security and privacy (cs.SI).
